{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d534da95-ece2-46db-ba1c-4542f8dcb11a","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** In xUnit, `Skip` is a property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, not a separate attribute. In the other three frameworks it's a standalone attribute placed alongside `[Test]`/`[TestMethod]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9887d2ac-19ce-459a-b011-4fdc6eb411f3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":334,"requestId":"340C:A4390:A585EE:C1EC98:69F3FF13"},"id":"7e8a0bc0-14ac-409f-bc86-a251ad022e16","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:17:14.718Z","parentId":"da3c2c5a-c004-44ae-a3cd-eb8603163821"}
